item.description:
**Position: ML Engineer** **Location: Fremont, CA (Onsite)** **Duration: 12\+ Months** **Job descripiton** **Technical Requirements** Tech Stack: Python;
Framework: FastAPI;
Architecture: REST APIs; Microservices;
**Experience Expectations** Year of Experience: P2 \- Mid\-Level \| 3\-5 years exp
Requirements: In\-depth expertise in Python for high\-performance, data\-intensive applications, PyTorch, Worked on Rag models
**Key Responsibilities** * Design, develop, and implement machine learning models using supervised learning techniques for design support and implementation * Collaborate with vehicle service and energy service and software teams * Take ownership of production models ensuring robust alerting systems for * Work with diverse, heterogeneous datasets (text, voice, images, tabular data) to scale * Translate ambiguous problem statements into actionable, end\-to\-end machine * Follow agile development practices and maintain high standards for clean, modular, and sustainable code
**Requirements** * 3\-5 years in\-depth expertise in Python for high\-performance, data\-intensive applications * Proficiency with at least one modern deep learning framework (e.g., PyTorch, JAX, TensorFlow) * Specialized knowledge in such areas as large language models, recommender * Strong foundational understanding of statistics for model comparison and * Real\-world experience deploying and maintaining production machine learning * Passion for writing clean, modular, and sustainable code to transition research * Degree in Computer Science, Data Science, or equivalent experience
